info.title: Jamf Pro Classic
info.description: This integration is designed to interact with the Jamf Pro Classic API

post.summary: Create Bearer Token
post.description: Create a Bearer token for use with other endpoints. This must be done before interaction with any other endpoints is allowed.

post.summary: Refresh Bearer Token
post.description: Invalidates existing token and generates a new token with extended expiration based on existing token credentials.

post.summary: Invalidate Current Token
post.description: Revokes and invalidates the token provided in the request.

get.summary: Get Details of Current Token
get.description: Get the authorization details associated with the current api token and selected site.

get.summary: Finds all accounts

schema.example: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0, post-check=0, pre-check=0

text/plain.example:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<accounts>
    <users>
        <user>
            <id>1</id>
            <name>admin</name>
        </user>
    </users>
    <groups/>
</accounts>

put.summary: Updates an existing group by ID
put.description: You cannot change information for an LDAP group.

post.summary: Creates a new group by ID
post.description: You cannot change information for an LDAP group.

delete.summary: Deletes a group by ID

schema.example: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0, post-check=0, pre-check=0

text/plain.example:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<user_group>
    <id>1</id>
</user_group>

put.summary: Updates an existing account by ID

post.summary: Creates a new account by ID

delete.summary: Deletes an account by ID

schema.example: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0, post-check=0, pre-check=0

text/plain.example:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<account>
    <id>2</id>
</account>

get.summary: Finds a subset of hardware/software reports by computer ID
get.description: Subset values can also be appended using an ampersand to return multiple subsets (e.g. /subsets/Software&Hardware)

parameters.name: dateRange
parameters.description: Range must be specified in the following format: yyyy-mm-dd_yyyy-mm-dd

parameters.name: subset
parameters.description: Supported values include: Software, Hardware, Fonts, Plugins

schema.example: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0, post-check=0, pre-check=0

get.summary: Finds a subset of hardware/software reports by computer name
get.description: Subset values can also be appended using an ampersand to return multiple subsets (e.g. /subsets/Software&Hardware)

parameters.name: dateRange
parameters.description: Range must be specified in the following format: yyyy-mm-dd_yyyy-mm-dd

parameters.name: subset
parameters.description: Supported values include: Software, Hardware, Fonts, Plugins

schema.example: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0, post-check=0, pre-check=0

get.summary: Finds a subset of hardware/software reports by computer UDID
get.description: Subset values can also be appended using an ampersand to return multiple subsets (e.g. /subsets/Software&Hardware)

parameters.name: dateRange
parameters.description: Range must be specified in the following format: yyyy-mm-dd_yyyy-mm-dd

parameters.name: subset
parameters.description: Supported values include: Software, Hardware, Fonts, Plugins

schema.example: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0, post-check=0, pre-check=0

get.summary: Finds a subset of hardware/software reports by computer serial number
get.description: Subset values can also be appended using an ampersand to return multiple subsets (e.g. /subsets/Software&Hardware)

parameters.name: dateRange
parameters.description: Range must be specified in the following format: yyyy-mm-dd_yyyy-mm-dd

parameters.name: subset
parameters.description: Supported values include: Software, Hardware, Fonts, Plugins

get.summary: Finds hardware/software reports by computer MAC address

parameters.name: dateRange
parameters.description: Range must be specified in the following format: yyyy-mm-dd_yyyy-mm-dd

schema.example: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0, post-check=0, pre-check=0

text/plain.example:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<computer_hardware_software_reports>
    <hardware_report>
        <date_time>2018/10/16 at 10:02 AM</date_time>

get.summary: Finds a subset of hardware/software reports by computer MAC address
get.description: Subset values can also be appended using an ampersand to return multiple subsets (e.g. /subsets/Software&Hardware)

parameters.name: dateRange
parameters.description: Range must be specified in the following format: yyyy-mm-dd_yyyy-mm-dd

parameters.name: subset
parameters.description: Supported values include: Software, Hardware, Fonts, Plugins

schema.example: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0, post-check=0, pre-check=0

get.summary: Finds a subset of computer history data by ID
get.description: Subset values can also be appended using an ampersand to return multiple subsets (e.g. /subsets/General&Commands)

parameters.name: subset
parameters.description: Supported values include: General, ComputerUsageLogs, Audits, PolicyLogs, CasperRemoteLogs, ScreenSharingLogs, CasperImagingLogs, Commands, UserLocation, MacAppStoreApplications

schema.example: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0, post-check=0, pre-check=0

text/plain.example:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<computer_history>
    <policy_logs>
        <policy_log>
            <policy_id>1</policy_id>
            <policy_name>Update Inventory</policy_name>

put.summary: Updates an existing mac application by ID
put.description: Does not support vpp codes.

post.summary: Creates a new mac application by ID
post.description: Does not support vpp codes.

schema.example:
<mac_application>
	<general>
		<id>1</id>
		<name>TextWrangler.app</name>
		<version>5.5.2</version>
		<is_free>true</is_free>
		<bundle_id>com.barebones.textwrangler</bundle_id>
		<url>https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/textwrangler/id404010395?mt=12&amp;uo=4</url>
		<category>
			<id>-1</id>
			<name>Unknown</name>
		</category>
		<site>
			<id>-1</id>
			<name>None</name>
		</site>
	</general>
	<scope>
		<all_computers>false</all_computers>
		<all_jss_users>false</all_jss_users>
	</scope>
	<self_service>
		<install_button_text>Install</install_button_text>

		<force_users_to_view_description>true</force_users_to_view_description>
		<self_service_icon></self_service_icon>

		<self_service_categories></self_service_categories>
		<notification>string</notification>

			<assign_vpp_device_based_licenses>false</assign_vpp_device_based_licenses>
			<vpp_admin_account_id>-1</vpp_admin_account_id>
		</vpp>
	</self_service>
</mac_application>

delete.summary: Deletes a mac application by ID

        <install_button_text>Install</install_button_text>
        <self_service_description>Minesweeper, a refreshingly clean, yet authentic interpretation of the classic strategy/puzzle game. The object of the game is to identify all mine squares by revealing all non-mine squares. The best minesweeper experience available.

FEATURES
- Beginner size preset (upgrade to the full version for five popular presets and custom)
- Save, load, and replay games.
- Mouse path is tracked with replay, and can be displayed.
- Window can be resized at any time
- Area is always opened on the first click.
- Double-click or press both buttons to reveal adjacent squares.
- A Right-click anywhere after a game, or click the clock to start a new game.
- Best times are tracked in a high score table.
- Chording is available for faster play.
- The Inspector tool shows live game statistics.
- Colors can be changed.

NOTICE
A mouse with two separate buttons is ideal for this game. If you use a trackpad or magic mouse, be sure to enable secondary clicks in your system preferences.</self_service_description>

put.summary: Updates an existing mac application by name
put.description: Does not support vpp codes.

delete.summary: Deletes a mac application by name

get.summary: Finds a subset of data for mac applications by name
get.description: Subset values can also be appended using an ampersand to return multiple subsets (e.g. /subsets/General&Scope)

parameters.name: subset
parameters.description: Supported values include: General, Scope, SelfService, VPPCodes, VPP

schema.example: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0, post-check=0, pre-check=0

text/plain.example:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<mac_application>
    <general>
        <id>1</id>
        <name>Minesweeper 101</name>
        <version>2.7.2</version>
        <is_free>true</is_free>
        <bundle_id>com.rossgame.Minesweeper-101</bundle_id>
        <url>https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/minesweeper-101/id432778614?mt=12&uo=4</url>
        <category>
            <id>3</id>
            <name>Apps</name>
        </category>
        <site>
            <id>-1</id>
            <name>None</name>
        </site>
        <deployment_type>Make Available in Self Service</deployment_type>
    </general>
</mac_application>

post.summary: Creates a new mobile device command
post.description:
The chart below includes additional requirements for usage of specific commands
| command | Parameters | Requirements | Values |
| ---------- | ------- | ------------ | ------ |
| DeviceName | device_name | Supervised Device | string |
| DeviceLocation | N/A | Supervised and in lost mode | N/A |
| DeviceLock | lock_message | optional | string |
| DisableLostMode | N/A | Supervised and in lost mode | N/A |
| EnableLostMode | lost_mode_message | Supervised device (required if lost_mode_phone is not set) | string |
| EnableLostMode | lost_mode_phone | Supervised device (required if lost_mode_message is not set) | string |
| EnableLostMode | lost_mode_footnote | optional | string |
| EnableLostMode | always_enforce_lost_mode | optional (defaults to 'true') | boolean |
| EnableLostMode | lost_mode_with_sound | optional (defaults to 'false') | boolean |
| EraseDevice | preserve_data_plan | optional (defaults to 'false') | boolean |
| EraseDevice | disallow_proximity_setup | optional (defaults to 'false') | boolean |
| EraseDevice | clear_activation_lock | optional (defaults to 'false') | boolean |
| PasscodeLockGracePeriod | passcode_lock_grace_period | Shared iPad | seconds (integer) |
| PlayLostModeSound | N/A | Supervised and in lost mode | N/A |
| RestartDevice | N/A | Supervised device | N/A |
| SettingsDisableBluetooth | N/A | iOS 11.3+ and Supervised | N/A |
| SettingsEnableBluetooth | N/A | iOS 11.3+ and Supervised | N/A |
| ShutDownDevice | N/A | Supervised device | N/A |
| Wallpaper | wallpaper_settings | Supervised device | 1 = Lock screen, 2 = Home screen, 3 = both |
| Wallpaper | wallpaper_id | Supervised device (required if wallpaper_content is not set) | Jamf Pro icon ID (integer) |
| Wallpaper | wallpaper_content | Supervised device (required if wallpaper_id is not set) | base64 encoded PNG or JPEG |

post.summary: Creates a new command to request that a mobile device update its OS. Command and mobile device list specified in URL. Device will be updated to the latest OS version based on device eligibility.

parameters.name: install_action
parameters.description: Specify the behavior of the install. Possible integer values are: 1 (Download the update for users to install), 2 (Download and install the update, and restart devices after installation)

parameters.name: id_list
parameters.description: Mobile device ID values, multiple IDs may be separated by commas (e.g. /id/13,14,15)

post.summary: Creates a new command to request that a mobile device update its OS. Command and mobile device list specified in URL. Mixing iOS and tvOS devices in ID list is not advised, as product version is specific to OS type.

parameters.name: install_action
parameters.description: Specify the behavior of the install. Possible integer values are: 1 (Download the update for users to install), 2 (Download and install the update, and restart devices after installation)

parameters.name: product_version
parameters.description: Specify the OS version of the update. Updating to a specific iOS version requires devices with iOS 11.3 or later. Updating to a specific tvOS version requires devices with tvOS 12.2 or later. install_action required by the ScheduleOSUpdate command if product_version is specified.

parameters.name: id_list
parameters.description: Mobile device ID values, multiple IDs may be separated by commas (e.g. /id/13,14,15)

get.summary: Finds a patch policy by ID

schema.example: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0, post-check=0, pre-check=0

text/plain.example:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<patch_policy>
    <general>
        <id>6</id>
        <name>Update Firefox</name>
        <enabled>true</enabled>
        <target_version>62.0</target_version>
        <release_date>1536141600516</release_date>
        <incremental_update>false</incremental_update>
        <reboot>false</reboot>
        <minimum_os>10.9</minimum_os>
        <kill_apps>
            <kill_app>
                <kill_app_name>Firefox.app</kill_app_name>
                <kill_app_bundle_id>org.mozilla.firefox</kill_app_bundle_id>
            </kill_app>
        </kill_apps>
        <distribution_method>prompt</distribution_method>
        <allow_downgrade>false</allow_downgrade>
        <patch_unknown>false</patch_unknown>
    </general>
    <scope>
        <all_computers>true</all_computers>
        <computers/>
        <computer_groups/>
        <users/>
        <buildings/>
        <departments/>
        <limitations>
            <network_segments/>
            <ibeacons/>
        </limitations>
        <exclusions>
            <computers/>
            <computer_groups/>
            <users/>
            <buildings/>
            <departments/>
            <network_segments/>
            <ibeacons/>
        </exclusions>
    </scope>
    <user_interaction>
        <grace_period>
            <grace_period_duration>15</grace_period_duration>
            <notification_center_subject>Important</notification_center_subject>
            <message>$APP_NAMES will quit in $DELAY_MINUTES minutes so that $SOFTWARE_TITLE can be updated. Save anything you are working on and quit the app(s).</message>
        </grace_period>
    </user_interaction>
    <software_title_configuration_id>12</software_title_configuration_id>
</patch_policy>
